criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. The patient and/or where relevant their parent/guardian/caretaker is willing and able
             to give informed consent /assent for participation in the study;

          2. Aged > 28 days (day of birth = Day 1);

          3. Axillary temperature at presentation ≥ 37.5°C OR axillary temperature at presentation
             < 35.5°C OR history of fever in last 24h (history of fever will apply to admitted
             patients only);

          4. Onset of illness ≤ 14 days

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Accident or trauma is the cause for the patient's presentation;

          2. Presentation ≤ 3 days after routine immunisations

          3. Already participated in this study
